				<li id="16714560" class="cmnt-root" data="25" data-d="1655184584000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579842/Miquellan-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">14 Jun 2022 01:29</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16714560" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Pulls the best damage from leveling Strength and Dex, but you still want to level faith a bit for increased damage with Sacred Blade. <br/><br/>At 35/35/35 it gets 589 AR one handed, 386 is phys, 202 in holy. <br/>At 43/42/20 it gets 602 AR one handed, 411 is phys, 190 is holy. <br/><br/>Note that this is for a 150 build, here&apos;s for a 120 for you PvP fellas: <br/>(Keep in mind that I am using 60 Vig and am on a Confessor for the starting class) <br/>At 30/30/25 it gets 563 AR onehanded, 369 is phys, 194 is holy. <br/>At 25/25/35 it gets 553 AR onehanded, 350 is phys, 202 is holy. <br/>Of course you can always take some health away and instead use that for damage, but the D scaling can only take you so far. <br/><br/>Generally speaking, you&apos;re better off investing into str and dex more so than faith. Even though each stat is D, the holy scaling only gets to D after some upgrades meaning that it&apos;s a lower D scaling than str and dex. If you want to take better advantage of Sacred Blade, it&apos;s probably better to just use the Alexander Shard. <br/><br/>My take away: not a terrible SS, in all honestly. In terms of pure AR it beats some of the lesser SS&apos;s, but it&apos;s split damage can be more of a bane than a boon for most cases. The unique R2 can be paired with the Axe talisman for good lunging attacks, and it&apos;s length isn&apos;t all too bad. My only wish is that it had higher scaling across the board, because D/D/D is pretty damn bad. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16714560" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16714560" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">5</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>25</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16714560"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16714560" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16714560"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
