				<li id="16672648" class="cmnt-root" data="8" data-d="1651975992000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579842/Miquellan-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">07 May 2022 22:13</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16672648" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Very underrated weapon. <br/>Yes sacred blade is a bit slow, but it can catch a lot of people off guard with good timing especially casters(500-600damage). <br/>For some odd reason in pvp from my experience at least, players seem to underestimate the fully charged heavy attack(600-800 damage).<br/>It also has high chance of breaking stance(really good for PVE mobs) and shields(PVE/PVP). <br/>Don&apos;t let the scaling fool you(it pretty much means nothing).<br/>If you don&apos;t mind distributing your attribute points to 3 different categories(STR/DEX/FAITH) then it might be a good weapon to try out. <br/><br/>TLDR Miquella&apos;s sword scaling is a lie, requires precise timing to be effective and 3 different attributes invested.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16672648" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16672648" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-righ