				<li id="16538500" class="cmnt-root" data="73" data-d="1647687512000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579842/Miquellan-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">19 Mar 2022 06:58</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16538500" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">So this sword gets a VERY bad wrap and you really need to look past the scaling letters.  The weapon art for this sword (which cannot be changed due to being a somber weapon) is Sacred Blade.  Sacred Blade in addition to letting you kill undead without an extra hit, doing bonus damage to undead, and shooting out a holy wave attack also buffs your weapon with additional holy damage.  That means this is a split damage sword that can actually be buffed by using it&apos;s weapon art, that&apos;s pretty rare.  But you can apply Sacred Blade to other weapons though, it exists as an Ash?  Right, however when standard weapons are turned Sacred their Str/Dex scaling falls to an abysmal E with C Faith scaling.  This sword retains D scaling across the board, and a higher base physical damage than any other straight sword when turned Sacred.  That&apos;s the trick, this isn&apos;t a Faith build sword, this is a Quality build sword that let&apos;s you do very high levels of Holy damage, and it will have higher AR than any quality straight sword unless you maybe get 60+ in both Dex/Str.   With the right build, once the weapon art is used, this sword will break 700 AR..... 700 AR on a straight sword.  It also has an interesting high stagger unique R2 attack using vertical swings.  So pay this weapon some respect, it is better than you think it is.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16538500" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16538500" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">5</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>79</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>6</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16538500"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16538500" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16538500"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
